Package sample

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Item
    An interface that sets up the getters and setters for Items that will be used in the program.
    MultimediaControl
    An interface that contains all four commands to be used with various products of certain types.
    ScreenSpec
    An interface setting up the getter methods to retrieve the aspects of a Product's Screen, if the Product has one.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AudioPlayer
    A class that has unique functionality for AudioPlayer products.
    Controller
    The Controller class holds almost all of the code that will be executed during this project, including event handling and connecting to the data base.
    Employee
    This class contains the information of employees, including their name, username and password.
    Main
    This program is made to simulate a product line.
    MoviePlayer
    A class that contains all MoviePlayer specific functionality.
    Product
    The main Product class that the majority of the program revolves around for data.
    ProductionRecord
    A class to assign every product a Production Number, a unique Product ID and Serial Number, as well as the date it was produced.
    Screen
    A class that holds the aspects of a Product's Screen, if it is of a Visual type.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    ItemType
    An Enum containing every ItemType we will use in the program.
    MonitorType
    An Enum containing the two types of monitors.
